ch.zhaw.swp2.stegano.model
Class ProtocolHeaderFactory

java.lang.Object
  ch.zhaw.swp2.stegano.model.ProtocolHeaderFactory

public class ProtocolHeaderFactory
extends Object

The BaseFileProtocolFactory calculates the Header, based on the Base-File and the Hidden-File, and has to be placed at the beginning of every modified Base-File

Author:
Renato Estermann

generateHeader

public static byte[] generateHeader(String inHiddenFileExtension,
                                    int inHiddenFileLength,
                                    byte inPollution)
                             throws IllegalArgumentException,
                                    IOException
This Method generates the Header and returns it in a Byte-Array.

Parameters:
inHiddenFileExtension - the File-Extension of the Hidden file. This String must have a length of 3. (e.t.: "txt" or "jpg")
inHiddenFileLength - the Length in Number of bytes of the HiddenFile
inPollution - one byte with the number of bit polluted.
Returns:
a Byte-Array representing the Header
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException
IOException

getLengthFromHeader

public static int getLengthFromHeader(byte[] inHeader)
                               throws IllegalArgumentException
Returns the Length (number of bytes) of the HiddenFile, which is in the Header

Parameters:
inHeader - the byte array with the Header
Returns:
the length (number of bytes) of the HiddenFile. The Algorithm has to process this number of bytes to get the whole HiddenFile out of the BaseFile.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the Header byte array has not the length of 8.

Returns the String with the File-Extension of the HiddenFile from the Header

Parameters:

Throws:
